    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>The estimated SARS-CoV-2 seroprevalence in children was found to be 9.46% for the Washington Metropolitan area. Hispanic/Latinx individuals were found to have higher odds of seropositivity. While chronic medical conditions were not associated with having antibodies, previous fever and body aches were predictive symptoms.</jats:p>",
